                        <p rend="center">SUMMARY OF CONCLUSIONS</p>
                        <p>1. <hi rend="italic">Diplomatic Strategy for Iran</hi>. The Department of
                            State presented a draft recommendation to the President outlining a
                            diplomatic strategy (Tab A).<note n="2" xml:id="d278fn2">Attached,
                                printed as <ref target="#d279">Document 279</ref>.</note> This
                            strategy is designed to keep lines open to <persName corresp="#p_BSAH_1">Bani-Sadr</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_GQS_1">Ghotbzadeh</persName> without offering any further concessions,
                            while encouraging the Europeans to persuade the clerics that it is in
                            their interest to find a resolution to the hostage issue. The <gloss target="#t_SCC_1">SCC</gloss> concurred with this recommendation,
                            recognizing that the chances of successfully persuading the Iranian
                            authorities to release the hostages are very slim. (S)</p>
                        <p> Approve the strategy outlined at Tab A.<note n="3" xml:id="d278fn3"><persName corresp="#p_CJ_1">Carter</persName> approved this
                                option with a checkmark and wrote in the right margin: “See notes.”
                                Reference is to the handwritten notes <persName corresp="#p_CJ_1">Carter</persName> made on the draft recommendation. See <ref target="#d279">Document 279</ref>.</note></p>
                        <p> Other </p>
                        <p>[<hi rend="italic">2 paragraphs (33 lines) not declassified</hi>]</p>
